Question: Find top 20 values in descendent order of a big map: :here's m codeInteger max = Collections.max(map.values());int count = 20;while(count>0){    for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> e : map.entrySet())        if(e.getValue() == max)        {            System.out.println(e.getKey() + "occurs" + e.getValue() + "times");            count--;        }        max--;}This program runs in theta of n square time complexity. Is there a better way to display entries in the max which have top 20 maximum values in descending order?
Please using this api: Iterator.next.
Answer: <<<api>>>: Iterator.next
<<<code>>>: 
Iterator<Map.Entry<String, Integer>> it = map.entrySet().iterator();
int max = 0;
int count = 20;
while (it.hasNext() && count > 0) {
    Map.Entry<String, Integer> pair = it.next();
    if (pair.getValue() > max) {
        max = pair.getValue();
        System.out.println(pair.getKey() + " occurs " + pair.getValue() + " times");
        count--;
    }
}
<<<explanation>>>: This program uses an iterator to go through each entry in the map. It checks if the value of the current entry is greater than the current max. If it is, it updates the max and prints the key and value. The loop continues until it has printed the top 20 entries with the highest values.
